#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Users and use cases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:3
msgid ""
"Open data is a means, not an end in itself. The first stage of any work with"
" OCDS is to consider who will use the data that is produced, and which "
"fields and features of the data are important to them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:5
msgid ""
"In designing OCDS, we explored a range of different user needs and use cases"
" for data on contracting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:7
msgid "We focussed on four main groups of user need:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:9
msgid "Achieving value for money for government"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:10
msgid ""
"Strengthening the transparency, accountability and integrity of public "
"contracting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:11
msgid "Enabling the private sector to fairly compete for public contracts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:12
msgid "Monitoring the effectiveness of service delivery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:14
msgid ""
"Some user needs are served by direct access to bulk data. To meet other user"
" needs will require tools built on top of OCDS data, providing interfaces, "
"visualisation, and links to spaces where users can engage with contracting "
"bodies and data publishers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:16
msgid ""
"You can read more about how people around the world are using OCDS, and "
"other contracting data, on the Open Contracting Partnership website. <!-- "
"TODO: Add links -->"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:18
msgid ""
"As you start implementing OCDS, consider how you will engage with data "
"users, and how you will ensure the data and documents you make available "
"will meet their needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Four example use cases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Value for money in procurement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:24
msgid ""
"<span "
"style=\"float:right\">![Person](../../../assets/icon_user.png)</span>Open "
"contracting data can help officials to get good value for money on the goods"
" and services in the procurement process, and can also help in identifying "
"whether value for money has been achieved in concluded contracts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:26
msgid ""
"These users want to analyze trends in prices and supplier performance, "
"including in terms of quality and duration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:28
msgid ""
"Comparable data using common codelists and the availability of unit prices "
"are particularly important for value for money use cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Detecting fraud and corruption"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:32
msgid ""
"<span "
"style=\"float:right\">![Person](../../../assets/icon_user.png)</span>All "
"stakeholders (civil society, the private sector, government and donors) have"
" an interest in identifying and combating corruption in public contracting. "
"Open contracting data can be used to scrutinize procurement documents and "
"data for ‘red flags’ that might indicate public monies are being mis-used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:34
msgid ""
"There are two main approaches to fraud and corruption monitoring. A ‘micro’ "
"approach closely scrutinizes individual procurements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:36
msgid ""
"A ‘systemic’ approach looks for suspicious patterns, and makes links between"
" datasets to map out networks of funding, ownership and interests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:38
msgid ""
"Data that can be linked up using globally unique identifiers for companies "
"is particularly important for fraud and corruption detection use cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Competing for public contracts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:42
msgid ""
"<span "
"style=\"float:right\">![Person](../../../assets/icon_user.png)</span>Open "
"contracting data can be used by private firms to understand the potential "
"pipeline of procurement opportunities. It is a core principle of open "
"contracting that information should be made available at the early stages of"
" a contracting process, including information on planned procurement, and "
"invitations for tenders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:44
msgid ""
"Information on past contracts can allow firms to identify upcoming "
"opportunities for re-contracting, and can support a more competitive "
"marketplace, as transparency creates a level playing field with information "
"on pricing, contract dates and key deliverables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:46
msgid ""
"Forward looking and timely information is particularly important for private"
" sector users, as well as being able to uniquely identify procuring "
"entities, geographic locations, sectors, and the kinds of items which are "
"being procured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Monitoring Service Delivery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:50
msgid ""
"<span "
"style=\"float:right\">![Person](../../../assets/icon_user.png)</span>Monitoring"
" groups want to ensure that public contracting delivers value to citizens in"
" terms of quality of goods, works, and services provided. To monitor "
"contracting effectively involves being able to link budgets and donor data "
"to the contracts and results. It also involves being able to verify whether "
"results are being delivered on the ground."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/getting_started/use_cases.md:52
msgid ""
"Data concerning budgets, delivery location and subcontracting arrangements "
"are particularly useful for those involved in contract monitoring."
msgstr ""
